					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7971109#post-4022364</guid>
				<title>the author post(tm)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7971109/its-all-coming-back-you-understand-i-don-t-like-it#post-4022364</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 12 Oct 2018 20:40:45 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>MrPines</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2241229</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Welcome to my Halloween entry. As with my first SCP, the title is a Sunny in Philadelphia quote. The piece itself is written in the style of rhyme royal, in which each stanza has a rhyme scheme of ABABBCC and each line has exactly 10 syllables. <sub>do not tempt the forghetti spaghetti</sub></p> <p>special thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-aers" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1856789&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1539376845" alt="Dr Aers" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1856789)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-aers" >Dr Aers</a></span> and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rounderhouse" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4187885&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1539376845" alt="Rounderhouse" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4187885)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rounderhouse" >Rounderhouse</a></span> for crit</p> <blockquote> <ul> <li><strong><span style="color: #090">The tale can only have one survivor; how you define that is up to you.</span></strong></li> <li><strong><span style="color: #090">The piece must start on Halloween and end during All Saints' Day sunrise.</span></strong></li> </ul> </blockquote> 
				 	]]>
